
[1]skolezite

   SKOL'EZITE, n. A mineral allied to Thomsonite, occurring crystallized
   and massive, colorless and nearly transparent. When a small portion of
   it is placed in the exterior flame of the blowpipe, it twists like a
   worm, becomes opake, and is converted into a blebby colorless glass.
